import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['wheat'])
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.title('What is the trend of wheat production over the years?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    avg_wheat_per_year = data.groupby('year')['wheat'].mean()
    avg_wheat_per_year.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average wheat production per year?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['wages'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Wages')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wages?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    pivot_data = data.pivot_table(index='year', columns='wheat', values='wages', aggfunc='count')
    plt.imshow(pivot_data, cmap='coolwarm', aspect='auto')
    plt.xlabel('Wheat Production')
    plt.ylabel('Year')
    plt.colorbar(label='Wages')
    plt.xticks(range(len(pivot_data.columns)), pivot_data.columns, rotation=90)
    plt.yticks(range(len(pivot_data.index)), pivot_data.index)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wheat production and year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
